body:
> Thanks for taking the time to report this.
> 
> Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?  (Must be openly licensed, completely self-contained so can directly run what you provide. Ideally use test_regress format, see https://veripool.org/guide/latest/contributing.html?highlight=test_regress#reporting-bugs)

Unfortunately I don't have a minimal repro that I can share. The following conditions are necessary but not sufficient to trigger the issue:
1. Hierarchical Verilation
2. ... while parsing arguments from a file
3. ... that contains `+incdir+` arguments
4. ... which the hier_block depends on

> What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

Verilating the hierarchical blocks fails with multiple errors of the form "Cannot find include file" [...] "This may be because there's no search path specified with `-I<dir>`."

When comparing the input `top.vc` file to the generated `*__hierMkArgs.f` files for the hierarchical blocks, all the `+incdir+` arguments are missing from the latter.

Disabling hierarchical Verilation makes the issue disappear, but at a high cost in compile time.

> What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

`verilator --cc --hierarchical -f top.vc`

> What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

v5.046 (first noticed in v5.040). Old notes (low confidence) suggest the issue may have been introduced in [3c8b8b65](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/commit/3c8b8b65d052562eba97e96afe6d88e2c3c97d4c).

> What OS and distribution are you using?

Ubuntu 20.04.1 (acknowledge EOL)

> May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

I have a minimal [patch](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25912183/allArgsStringForHierBlock.patch) that resolves the issue by iterating over `m_allArgs` instead of `m_lineArgs` but I'm not sure whether that's too broad:

```diff
diff --git a/src/V3Options.cpp b/src/V3Options.cpp
index 246aee89e..065e0937c 100644
--- a/src/V3Options.cpp
+++ b/src/V3Options.cpp
@@ -437,7 +437,8 @@ string V3Options::allArgsStringForHierBlock(bool forTop) const {
     string out;
     bool stripArg = false;
     bool stripArgIfNum = false;
-    for (const string& arg : m_impp->m_lineArgs) {
+    for (const auto& pair : m_impp->m_allArgs) {
+      for (const string& arg : pair.first) {
         if (stripArg) {
             stripArg = false;
             continue;
@@ -471,6 +472,7 @@ string V3Options::allArgsStringForHierBlock(bool forTop) const {
         // Don't use opt here because '-' is removed in arg
         // Use double quote because arg may contain whitespaces
         out += '"' + VString::quoteAny(arg, '"', '\\') + '"';
+      }
     }
     return out;
 }
```

